He also gave the boy part of an oatmeal raisin cookie until workers from the Department of Human Services arrived.

Clark called the TriMet's operation command center to tell them what had happened, and he was told to drive to the Gresham Central Transit Center nearby because he was blocking traffic.

The little boy, who is named James, was reunited with his father, who called police to report the boy missing.

He explained that he works night shifts and had fallen asleep when the boy let himself out of the apartment and wandered into the road. The boy's mother was already at work.

