DHS workers interviewed the parents, who were not charged with anything, and told them to install child locks to prevent a similar situation.

Transit police submitted a commendation for Clark - who has worked for the company for seven year - but he insisted that he is not a hero.

'I don't like that label,' he said. 'I just did what I think anybody should do or would have done under the same circumstances.'

